  "text": "and E[1 + ℓ(η)/p] = 1 + 1/p. Therefore, for the stochastic program [CITATION_1] , conditions (i) and (iii) are easily satisfied. However, condition (ii) does not hold since the optimization (17) is subject to an unbounded support R. So the consistency results in (3.1) cannot be applied to our problem directly. To circumvent this, we rewrite the stochastic optimization (17) as a stochastic optimization problem over a compact set. ",
